Package: cascsim
Title: CAS Individual Claim Simulator
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Robert", "Bear", email = "rbear@reserveprism.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Kailan", "Shang", email = "klshang81@gmail.com", role = c("aut","cre")),
    person("Hai", "You", email = "hyou@reserveprism.com", role = "aut"))
Description: It is an open source insurance claim simulation engine sponsored
    by the Casualty Actuarial Society and built by ReservePrism LLC. It generates 
	individual insurance claims including open claims, reopened claims, IBNR 
	claims and UPR claims. It also includes claim data fitting functions to 
	help set simulation assumptions. It is useful for claim level reserving analysis.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: parallel, R2HTML, fitdistrplus, moments, copula, scatterplot3d, methods
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
